The paper proposes a novel way to predict stock market prices using machine learning algorithms, specifically ensemble learning. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves feature extraction and classification, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the use of decision trees and OOB error estimation suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
